4. nec quicquam quam si...alereutur. Supply ezercitus, “just as much as if the armies were still supported out of a rich treasury.'’

5. Iliturgi oppidum: a city of Hispania Boetica, about five days’ march from Carthago Nova. Having joined the Romans, it was twice besieged by the Carthaginians (see again, Bk. xfflv. cb. xli.)‚ but each time the siege was raised. At last, on the overthrow of the two Scipios‚ it revolted to the Carthaginians, for which the inhabitants were put to the swerd, and the city burnt by P. Scipio, 13.c. 206.
